# P8-I7: User Acceptance Testing (UAT)

## Overview

**Task ID**: P8-I7  
**Phase**: Phase 8 - Integration & Polish  
**Priority**: P0 (Critical)  
**Status**: ⬜ Todo  
**Description**: Comprehensive User Acceptance Testing to validate production readiness

**Objective**: Conduct thorough user acceptance testing to ensure VJLive3 meets all functional, performance, and usability requirements for real-world VJ performance scenarios. Validate that the application is ready for production deployment and end-user adoption.

---

## What This Module Does

This task orchestrates a complete User Acceptance Testing (UAT) campaign to verify that VJLive3:

1. **Meets User Needs**: All core VJ workflows are functional and intuitive
2. **Performs Acceptably**: 60 FPS maintained under realistic load conditions
3. **Handles Edge Cases**: Graceful degradation when hardware/resources are limited
4. **Is Production-Ready**: All critical bugs resolved, documentation complete
5. **Validates P8-I6**: Confirms that production deployment validation findings are addressed

This is a **validation and coordination** task - no new code is written. Instead, existing functionality is tested against real-world scenarios, user feedback is collected and analyzed, and a final UAT sign-off report is generated.

