### 2. Performance Under Load

**Objective**: Verify 60 FPS is maintained under realistic performance conditions.

**Test Matrix**:

| Configuration | Video Sources | Effects Chain | Resolution | Expected FPS |
|---------------|---------------|---------------|------------|--------------|
| Minimal | 1 | 2 | 1920×1080 | ≥58 |
| Typical | 3 | 6 | 1920×1080 | ≥58 |
| Heavy | 4 | 10 | 1920×1080 | ≥55 |
| Stress | 4 | 12 | 3840×2160 | ≥50 |

**Performance Metrics to Capture**:

```bash
# Monitor FPS, memory, CPU in real-time
python scripts/monitor_performance.py --duration 300 --output uat_perf_metrics.json

# Key metrics:
# - Frame time variance (p50, p95, p99)
# - Memory usage (RSS, VMS, GPU memory)
# - CPU usage per core
# - Disk I/O (if recording)
# - Network throughput (if NDI/WebSocket active)
```

**Acceptance Criteria**:
- **FPS**: ≥58 FPS p50, ≥55 FPS p95 in Typical configuration
- **Frame Time**: ≤16.67ms p95, ≤33.34ms p99 (no stutters)
- **Memory**: ≤200MB Python heap, ≤500MB total RSS (no leaks over 10min)
- **CPU**: ≤80% total, ≤90% any single core (no thermal throttling)
- **GPU Memory**: ≤2GB (NVIDIA) or ≤1GB (AMD integrated)
- **Startup Time**: ≤5 seconds from launch to first frame
- **Shutdown Time**: ≤3 seconds (clean exit, no zombie processes)

**Stress Tests**:
- Run for 2 hours continuously, monitor for memory leaks
- Rapid plugin chain reconfiguration (100 changes in 5min)
- Simultaneous recording + streaming + effects
- Hot-reload 20 plugins in succession

