### 8. Recovery and Resilience

**Objective**: Verify application recovers gracefully from failures.

**Failure Scenarios to Test**:

| Failure | Trigger | Expected Recovery | Max Downtime |
|---------|---------|-------------------|--------------|
| Plugin crash | Kill plugin process | Reload plugin, continue playback | <2 seconds |
| GPU driver reset | `nvidia-smi --gpu-reset` | Detect reset, reinitialize GL context | <5 seconds |
| Depth camera disconnect | Unplug USB | Show warning, continue without depth | Immediate |
| Audio device loss | Disconnect audio interface | Switch to fallback device | <1 second |
| Disk full | Fill disk to 100% | Stop recording, alert user, continue playback | Immediate |
| Out of memory | Allocate until OOM | Graceful degradation, kill least-recent plugin | <3 seconds |
| Network loss | Unplug Ethernet (NDI/OSC) | Queue messages, reconnect automatically | <10 seconds |
| Power loss (laptop) | Unplug power, run on battery | Continue without throttling (if battery >20%) | N/A |

**Recovery Validation**:
- No data loss on crash recovery (presets, settings saved)
- Auto-recovery of last session on restart
- Clear error messages with actionable guidance
- No "silent failures" (all errors logged and user-visible if impactful)

