## Success Criteria

### Minimum Requirements for "Pass"

1. **All Core Scenarios Pass**: ≥90% of UAT-CORE scenarios pass on ≥80% of hardware profiles
2. **Performance**: FPS ≥55 p95 in Typical configuration on ≥80% of test hardware
3. **Critical Bugs**: Zero P0 (blocker) bugs, ≤3 P1 (major) bugs with workarounds
4. **User Satisfaction**: Average rating ≥3.5/5.0 from participants
5. **Documentation**: All major features documented, new user tutorial ≤15min
6. **Recovery**: All failure scenarios recover within specified time limits
7. **Integration**: All external system integrations (NDI, OSC, DMX, MIDI) functional

### "Go/No-Go" Decision

**Go Production IF**:
- ✅ All minimum requirements met
- ✅ No P0 bugs
- ✅ ≤5 P1 bugs (with acceptable workarounds)
- ✅ Performance acceptable on ≥80% of target hardware
- ✅ ≥70% of participants would use in live performance

**No-Go (Requires Fixes) IF**:
- ❌ Any P0 bug exists
- ❌ FPS <50 on typical hardware
- ❌ >10 P1 bugs
- ❌ <50% of participants would use in live performance
- ❌ Critical documentation missing

**Conditional Go** (with post-launch fixes):
- ⚠️ Minor bugs exist but don't block core workflows
- ⚠️ Some hardware incompatibility (specify unsupported configurations)
- ⚠️ Documentation gaps (specify what to add in first patch)

