## Troubleshooting Guide

### Common UAT Issues

**Issue**: Application crashes during scenario execution  
**Diagnosis**: Check `logs/vjlive3_uat_<timestamp>.log` for stack trace  
**Action**: Reproduce with `gdb --args python -m vjlive3.main`, collect core dump  
**Workaround**: Try simpler configuration (fewer effects, lower resolution)

**Issue**: FPS consistently below threshold  
**Diagnosis**: Run `python scripts/profile_fps.py --detailed` to identify bottleneck  
**Action**: Check GPU driver version, update if outdated; reduce effect chain complexity  
**Workaround**: Lower output resolution, disable heavy effects (raymarch, particles)

**Issue**: Depth camera not detected  
**Diagnosis**: `lsusb` (Linux) or Device Manager (Windows) to verify USB device  
**Action**: Ensure USB3 port (blue insert), reinstall Astra drivers  
**Workaround**: Use simulated depth source for testing

**Issue**: MIDI controller not responding  
**Diagnosis**: `python -m vjlive3.tools.midi_listener` to see if MIDI messages arrive  
**Action**: Check MIDI device is selected in VJLive3 settings, not exclusive mode  
**Workaround**: Use virtual MIDI loopback for testing

**Issue**: NDI streams lagging or dropping  
**Diagnosis**: Check network bandwidth (1 Gbps minimum), NDI tools monitor  
**Action**: Reduce NDI resolution/bitrate, use wired network not WiFi  
**Workaround**: Use local video files instead of NDI

**Issue**: DMX output not working  
**Diagnosis**: `python -m vjlive3.tools.dmx_monitor` to see if DMX frames transmitted  
**Action**: Verify DMX interface is ArtNet/sACN compatible, check IP configuration  
**Workaround**: Use DMX simulator for testing

**Issue**: WebSocket remote disconnects frequently  
**Diagnosis**: Check browser console for WebSocket errors, network tab  
**Action**: Ensure stable network, increase WebSocket ping interval  
**Workaround**: Use localhost instead of network IP if testing on same machine

**Issue**: Audio latency too high (>50ms)  
**Diagnosis**: `python scripts/measure_audio_latency.py` loopback test  
**Action**: Use ASIO driver on Windows, JACK on Linux; reduce buffer size  
**Workaround**: Accept higher latency for non-performative testing

